beer.beer_description: Tropical Style Stout - formerly considered a subcategory of the Foreign Extra Stout, this stout is noted for it's use of indigenous grains and sugar additions (most popularly in the West Indies) of the Caribbean and Africa.

Our new single hopped DIPA series, Sole Accomplice. This first round is brewed with 100% Mosaic. Huge tangerine and grapefruit flavors intermingle with a hint of sweetness from notes of mango and berries. Rounded out by an earthy and herbal undertone, this one illustrates every tile of the Mosaic hop.
We’ve taken the famously quaffable characteristics of the prolific American Lager and merged them with the bright, bursting flavors of an American Craft Beer. Crisp, crushable, and easy drinking.
Using 100% Nelson Sauvin hops, the signature aroma of grape juice is accompanied by the same nuanced sweetness in the taste.

Dark amber red in color, this traditional Irish Red is layered with subtle sweetness. Conservative use of English hops give the malt forward flavors a balanced earthy tone. Full bodied notes of caramel and brown sugar give way to a deceptively light and clean finish.
Born on a Monday, this Double IPA blends Simcoe, Citra, and Amarillo to create a potent fruit juice blend. Mild bitterness and a pleasant hint of floral and pine notes finishes this one out.
Bursting with Tropical Fruit and a Kiss of Bitterness
Dry hopped saison

We used Citra, Lemondrop, and Centennial hops in this one to really push forward a lemon flavor while maintaining an overall balance. Light with a dry and crisp finish, mild oat presence gives the beer enough of a malt body to know it's there while not stealing the show.
Corrosive Haze is a Sour IPA, fruited with Cherries, Blueberries, and Strawberries.

We took our dark saison, packed with flavors of dried plum and dates and conditioned it on black currants. Forward flavors of Cabernet Sauvignon blend with a mildly sweet acidity and the base saison to add another layer of complexity to an already multi-faceted beer.
Pink Guava Gose
A neutral yeast profile allows the full bodied presence of the whet to take center stage. Lemon and lime zest compliments this smooth drinking ale without overpowering the base beer.

We wanted to bring you a low ABV IPA that still packs all the flavorful hop forward punch that you would expect in an IPA. Enter Accidental Sessions. At 4.6% we added a small amount of lactose to help this beer maintain a big enough body, without being overly sweet, to support the heavy dose of hops we hit it with. Packer with El Dorado, Nelson Sauvin, and Citra you'll get the full experience of an IPA, but you can drink it all day.
